    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A gear-driven drilling instrument which inserts a three-millimeter-diameter probe into a tree, and graphically or digitally records resistance to the probe; used to detect decay and defects.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
